<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1854,2025]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1854,1881]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Some interfrontal setulae longer than lowest setulae on ocellar triangle (ch.3-2); arista without apical expansion (ch.7-0; 
<figureCitation box="[370,461,1891,1917]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,525,1774]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,525,1779]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 4. Phortica (Ashima) andreagigoni Toda &amp; Bänziger, sp. nov. (♂ holotype). A, Antenna; B, periphallic organs (cau- dolateral view); C, aedeagus, phallapodeme, hypandrium and pregonite (lateral view); D, aedeagal sheath, postgonites, hypandrium and pregonites (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884622" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884622/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); pregonite strongly curved ventrad distally (
<figureCitation box="[973,1064,1891,1917]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,525,1774]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,525,1779]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 4. Phortica (Ashima) andreagigoni Toda &amp; Bänziger, sp. nov. (♂ holotype). A, Antenna; B, periphallic organs (cau- dolateral view); C, aedeagus, phallapodeme, hypandrium and pregonite (lateral view); D, aedeagal sheath, postgonites, hypandrium and pregonites (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884622" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884622/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
); posterior postgonites on lateral lobes of aedeagal sheath medially fused to each other (ch.66-1; 
<figureCitation box="[886,978,1927,1953]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,525,1774]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,525,1779]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 4. Phortica (Ashima) andreagigoni Toda &amp; Bänziger, sp. nov. (♂ holotype). A, Antenna; B, periphallic organs (cau- dolateral view); C, aedeagus, phallapodeme, hypandrium and pregonite (lateral view); D, aedeagal sheath, postgonites, hypandrium and pregonites (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884622" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884622/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
); left and right lateral lobes of aedeagal sheath with 1 and 2 anterior, somewhat triangular, plate-like postgonites, respectively (
<figureCitation box="[1123,1214,1963,1989]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,525,1774]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,525,1779]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 4. Phortica (Ashima) andreagigoni Toda &amp; Bänziger, sp. nov. (♂ holotype). A, Antenna; B, periphallic organs (cau- dolateral view); C, aedeagus, phallapodeme, hypandrium and pregonite (lateral view); D, aedeagal sheath, postgonites, hypandrium and pregonites (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884622" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884622/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1854,2025]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1437,153,503]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1998,2025]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Description</emphasis>
(not repeating characters common to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Chen &amp; Maca" authorityYear="2012" box="[772,895,1999,2025]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foliiseta">
<emphasis box="[772,789,2000,2025]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[805,895,1999,2025]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">foliiseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Supracervical setae 14–15. Dorsomedial, tentorial apodeme 2/3 as long as basal, parallel portion of dorsolateral, tentorial apodeme. Longest, dorsal branch of arista shorter than longest seta on pedicel (
<figureCitation box="[636,728,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,525,1774]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,525,1779]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 4. Phortica (Ashima) andreagigoni Toda &amp; Bänziger, sp. nov. (♂ holotype). A, Antenna; B, periphallic organs (cau- dolateral view); C, aedeagus, phallapodeme, hypandrium and pregonite (lateral view); D, aedeagal sheath, postgonites, hypandrium and pregonites (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884622" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884622/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Fore and hind tarsomere Is slightly longer than 3 succeeding tarsomeres together; mid one as long as rest tarsomeres together.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,153,503]" box="[199,1127,260,287]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
