<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,1947,2045]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1947,1973]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Chen &amp; Maca" authorityYear="2012" box="[586,707,1947,1974]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foliiseta">
<emphasis box="[586,603,1948,1973]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[617,707,1947,1973]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">foliiseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the cluster of the four species, in having the dorsomedial, tentorial apodeme ≥ 2/3 basal, parallel portion of dorsolateral, tentorial apodeme (ch.1-0), but can be distinguished from it by the diagnostic characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
